column1:
Instructions: prepare a spreadsheet of the subsidy-eligible and potentially eligible children in your child care program(s). This includes those currently applying or expected to apply for subsidy. If you don't have all this information right now, just leave it blank. You will be able to fill it in later. 

Useful resources for finding this information include: subsidy approval letters from the state, child roster reports from child care management software like Brightwheel and ProCare
